From: Lans Zhang <jia.zhang@windriver.com>
Date: Tue, 19 Nov 2013 14:44:54 +0800
Subject: [PATCH] Fix calltrace triggered durning capsule update.

Signed-off-by: Lans Zhang <jia.zhang@windriver.com>
---
 arch/x86/platform/efi/efi_capsule.c |    2 +-
 1 files changed, 1 insertions(+), 1 deletions(-)
 mode change 100644 => 100755 arch/x86/platform/efi/efi_capsule.c

diff --git a/arch/x86/platform/efi/efi_capsule.c b/arch/x86/platform/efi/efi_capsule.c
old mode 100644
new mode 100755
index d329d6d..3eb3a64
--- a/arch/x86/platform/efi/efi_capsule.c
+++ b/arch/x86/platform/efi/efi_capsule.c
@@ -87,7 +87,7 @@ static int efi_capsule_trigger_update(void)
 	pr_info(PFX"File %s size %u descriptor blocks %u\n",
 		fpath, total_size, nblocks);
 
-	data = kmalloc(nblocks, GFP_KERNEL);
+	data = kzalloc(nblocks * sizeof(u8 *), GFP_KERNEL);
 	if (data == NULL){
 		ret = -ENOMEM;
 		pr_info("Failed to allocate %d bytes\n", nblocks);
